snippet.textDisplay:
On the subject a Katamari game for WiiU  a little further down in the comments (because I can't reply to the ones I want to)...
A Nintendo Katamari game would easily be one of my favorite games on the WiiU, and hey! It might not be so far fetched of an idea anymore, with Nintendo and Namco Bandai getting all friendly-like in the making of Smash Bros 4
All we can do is make noise, and hope enough of us want the game for them to see a legitimate market for it.

snippet.textDisplay: Someone said this game is super short and barely has any content. That's unfortunate, I'll probably only pick it up if I find it very cheap. The Katamari series seems to be on a bit of a break since it's been struggling sales-wise. There's some wasted potential here, it feels like they're sitting on the first game's same old (but fun) concept. They should try to make a new game that could reach a higher level of quality by expanding the concept. Maybe for the Wii U?
